Whisk together @water{1/2%cup}, @tomato paste{2%tbsp}, @crushed tomatoes{1%13.76oz can},
@beef stock concentrate{4}, @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, @Southwest spice blend{2%tbsp},
and a few large pinches of @salt{} inside your #slow cooker{}.

> We sent more tomato paste and paprika. Use the rest of the paste as you like. Save the
> rest of the paprika for later.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(peeled and diced).
Core, seed, and dice @green bell pepper{2}(diced). Stir both ingredients into broth
in slow cooker.

Break up @ground beef{20%oz} with your hands into crumbles, then add to slow cooker.
Gently stir once or twice to incorporate. Cover slow cooker with lid and cook on
high heat for ~{6%hours} or low heat for ~{8%hours}.

Around the same time chili is done cooking, drain @black beans{1%13.4oz can} from
container and rinse, then stir into chili in slow cooker. Season with @salt{} and
@black pepper{}.

Stir together remaining @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} and @sour cream{6%tbsp} in a
#small bowl{}. Season with @salt{}.

Wrap @corn tortillas{6} in a damp #paper towel{}. Microwave on high until warm,
~{30-45%seconds}.

Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Divide chili
between #bowls{}, then dollop with crema. Sprinkle with scallions and
@Monterey Jack cheese{3/4%cup}. Serve with tortillas on the side for dipping.